  "text": "Hence, spleen dysfunctions such as splenomegaly, blood-based leukemias, and asplenia have been conventionally identified [CITATION_1] . In the present study, animal fed with MCF-MORS showed no visible lesions to the spleen cells, that is, normal visible splenocytes ( Figure 13 ). This asserts a better physiological wellness of T and B lymphocytes, granulocytes, dendritic cells, macrophages, and other immune cells [CITATION_2] ) than UF-MOS.",
